Description: Fix CVE-2026-49218 - Missing check for zero columns/rows in DCM coder
 The DCM (DICOM) image reader did not validate that the decoded image
 had non-zero dimensions before returning it. Returning an image with
 zero columns or rows could lead to undefined behaviour in downstream
 consumers. Add an explicit check and raise CorruptImageError /
 ImproperImageHeader when either dimension is zero.
 .
