 ImageMagick's AcquireAlignedMemory() did not enforce the configured maximum
 memory request ceiling. An attacker able to influence allocation size via a
 crafted image could trigger an excessively large aligned allocation,
 bypassing the global memory cap and causing memory exhaustion / denial of
 service (CWE-770).
